<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,546,2011]" box="[151,935,546,571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Total length 6.9 mm (male holotype), 6.8 mm (male paratypes, n = 2).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,546,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[274,353,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[365,394,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 29" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1653,1676]" captionTargetBox="[184,1378,948,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,916,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 29. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 26, Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov., male holotype (total length 6.7 mm). 27, D. sakakibara sp. nov., male holotype (t. l. 6.9 mm). 28, D. segmentalis (Signoret, 1853), male (t. l. 9.0 mm). 29, D. trinotatus (Signoret, 1853), female (t. l. 9.0 mm). The last three species belong to the trinotatus group (see text for details)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816005/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">27</figureCitation>
) well produced anteriorly; frons with muscle impressions distinct. Hind legs with meron not exposed. Other features of head and thorax much as described above for 
<taxonomicName authority="Quintas &amp; Felix &amp; Lima &amp; Mejdalani, 2017" authorityName="Quintas &amp; Felix &amp; Lima &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2017" box="[966,1081,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dilobopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nelsoni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[966,1081,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. nelsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1088,1178,618,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1088,1178,618,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,546,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
Color (
<figureCitation box="[280,404,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Figs. 9–10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[418,450,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 29" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1653,1676]" captionTargetBox="[184,1378,948,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,916,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 29. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 26, Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov., male holotype (total length 6.7 mm). 27, D. sakakibara sp. nov., male holotype (t. l. 6.9 mm). 28, D. segmentalis (Signoret, 1853), male (t. l. 9.0 mm). 29, D. trinotatus (Signoret, 1853), female (t. l. 9.0 mm). The last three species belong to the trinotatus group (see text for details)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816005/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">27</figureCitation>
). Ground color of anterior dorsum dark brown to black. Crown with yellow marks as follows: pair of strongly curved stripes on posterior half of disc, pair of elongate, anteriorly convergent marks near anterior margin, pair of spots just before anterior eye angles, pair of spots at posterior margin, and smaller marks on areas of muscle impressions of frons and behind eyes. Pronotum with two transverse rows of four yellow spots near anterior margin, spots of anterior row smaller than those of posterior row. Mesonotum with large yellow area on posterior portion of scutum and covering much of scutellum. Forewings dark brown; with large yellow mark on basal third of clavus, adjacent to that of mesonotum when wings are at rest, and much smaller yellow mark on wing base; with large subrectangular vitreous area on basal half extending from costal margin to apical portion of clavus, allowing observation of two large transverse yellow areas of abdominal tergum; apical cells hyaline. Ground color of face dark brown to black; superior half of frons yellow below antennal ledges and with yellow arcs at region of muscle impressions; genae yellow below eyes, this yellow area extending posteriorly over pro- and mesothorax. Ventral region of thorax, including basal portions of legs, mostly dark brown to black; pro- and mesofemora dark brown to black basally, most of hind femora dark brown, hind coxae with large yellow mark on outer lateral portion. Abdomen, in ventral view, with sternites dark brown, their posterior margins yellow; most of laterotergites yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,546,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
Male genitalia. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[488,572,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly; posterior margin narrowly rounded; without processes; with numerous dispersed macrosetae absent only on basal fourth. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, subtriangular; not extending as far posteriorly as pygofer apex; separated from each other throughout their length; with multiseriate macrosetae on ventral surface, microsetae also present. Connective (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped but with stalk directed dorsoanteriorly; without median keel. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1318,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, elongate, extending posteriorly distinctly farther than apex of connective; with preapical lobe bearing few setae; apex finger-shaped, directed outwards. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[811,896,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, with well developed dorsal lobe; without processes; gonoduct distinct; gonopore located apically. Paraphyses (
<figureCitation box="[1292,1428,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1434,1457]" captionTargetBox="[184,1434,391,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,375,1412]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Dilobopterus sakakibara sp. nov. 9, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 10, forewing. 11 – 16, male genitalia. 11, pygofer, lateral view. 12, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 13, connective and style, dorsal view. 14, ejaculatory reservoir and aedeagus, lateral view. 15, paraphyses, laterodorsal view (setae of one ramus omitted). 16, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 9 = 1 mm, 10 = 2 mm, 11 – 16 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816001/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Figs. 15–16</figureCitation>
) with rami slightly asymmetrical and bearing numerous conspicuous setae on apical portion.
</paragraph>
